companyProfile.companyDescription: Tata Motors Limited is an India-based global automobile manufacturer of cars, utility vehicles, pick-ups, trucks, and buses, offering a range of integrated, smart, and e-mobility solutions. The Company’s segments include Automotive and Others. The Automotive segment consists of four reportable sub-segments: Tata Commercial Vehicles, Tata Passenger Vehicles, Jaguar Land Rover and Vehicle Financing. Its automotive business includes all activities relating to the development, design, manufacture, assembly and sale of vehicles, as well as related spare parts and accessories, and distribution and service of vehicles. The Others segment consists of information technology services and insurance broking services. With operations in India, the United Kingdom, South Korea, Thailand, and Indonesia, the Company markets its vehicles in Africa, the Middle East, Latin America, Southeast Asia, and the South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) countries.

recentNews.headline: Rush to buy rare earth magnets at a premium cushioned blow from China curbs
recentNews.intro: In response to tensions over trade with the US, China imposed a restriction on the export of rare earth magnets starting 4 April. What was initially thought to be a move aimed at the US soon engulfed Indian suppliers as well.
recentNews.imagecaption: India imported 53,740 tonnes of permanent magnets in FY25, a rise of 88%.

recentNews.headline: Chinese motors instead of Chinese magnets? Yes, but there's a problem
recentNews.intro: Desperate automakers are looking to import fully made Chinese motors. But they attract a higher duty, and may disqualify from them subsidy schemes. What's the solution?
recentNews.imagecaption: Electric vehicles are powered by traction motors connected to a battery, while sensors, telemetry and other electronic functions of all vehicles use rare earth magnets.

recentNews.imagecaption: There are multiple modern technologies that the Harrier EV gets which are unique to the electric SUV.

recentNews.headline: Tata Motors to Syngene- Prashanth Tapse suggests stocks to buy in the short term
recentNews.intro: Indian stocks traded lower as investors awaited a trade agreement with the US and assessed SEBI's action against Jane Street. Nifty 50 rose 0.04% to 25,415.45, while Sensex increased 0.05%. Prashanth Tapse recommends buying Tata Motors, GRSE, Syngene, and Sigachi in the near-term.
recentNews.imagecaption: Tata Motors to Syngene- Prashanth Tapse suggests stocks to buy in the short term

recentNews.headline: Creta can?t carry Hyundai forever; Korean giant risks losing No. 2 spot in India
recentNews.intro: Long, long ago, it had the Santro. And now it has the Creta. But aside from this mid-size SUV, none of Hyundai?s vehicles is making much headway in India today. And that has pushed it down the rankings this year. Can the carmaker make a comeback?
recentNews.imagecaption: An assembly line worker at a Hyundai Motor India plant. The company currently operates two integrated plants near Chennai.

recentNews.headline: Have  ?10,000 to invest? Here are four stocks to explore for the long term.
recentNews.intro: Many investors are waiting for the market to fall substantially to start investing. But with a little research, investors can still find plenty of good stocks trading at reasonable valuations, even in the current market.
recentNews.imagecaption: Investing  ?10,000 in stocks today may seem challenging as the market continues its rally. Image: Pixabay

recentNews.headline: Auto stocks to buy: Maruti Suzuki, M&M, TVS, Eicher Motors among top stock picks after June sales data
recentNews.intro: Retail demand saw only modest year-on-year (YoY) growth in PVs, CVs, and 2Ws, while export performance remained a bright spot ? especially in the 2W and PV segments. Among OEMs, Mahindra & Mahindra (M&M), TVS Motor Company, and Eicher Motors stood out with strong YoY growth.
recentNews.imagecaption: In the PV space, M&M emerged as the only listed player to post YoY volume growth in June (+18% in utility vehicles), while Maruti Suzuki India, Tata Motors, and Hyundai Motor India reported volume declines.
